The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Carlisle ton in drawn tie 
Bulawayo: Zimbabwe won the two-Test series against Bangladesh 1-0 as the second Test fizzled out in a tame draw on the final day at Queens Sports Club on Monday. Stuart Carlisle did his best to liven up proceedings as he completed his second Test century  103, including a six and nine fours  and he figured in a second wicket partnership of 129 with Trevor Gripper, who made 65.Grant Flower too got among the runs. Bangladesh were earlier all out for 168 with Manzural Islam Rana scoring 39. Mohammed Rafique contributed an unbeaten 26.  (AFP)  Copyright 
